OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,415,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1784233115
OL,3,CRisk of 'Treasury always chickens out'
OL,4,Cmentality at Stormont, MPs told
OL,6,FMinisters have consistently made the
OL,7,Fpoint that they need more funding from
OL,8,Fthe Treasury to address a funding
OL,9,Fcrisis facing public services in
OL,10,FNorthern Ireland.
OL,12,FAfter the Executive exceeded its
OL,13,Fbudget in the previous financial year,
OL,14,Fthe UK Government allocated #400
OL,15,Fmillion to deal with overspend
OL,16,Fpressures, to be repaid over the next
OL,17,Fthree years, and the Treasury
OL,18,Fconducted an "open-book exercise"
OL,19,Flooking at the Executive budget.
OL,26,@zD@NOUzD@aO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/15
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,415,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1784233115
OL,3,CRisk of 'Treasury always chickens out'
OL,4,Cmentality at Stormont, MPs told
OL,6,FAsked why this exercise was not
OL,7,Fcompleted earlier by his department,
OL,8,FMr Benn told the Northern Ireland
OL,9,FAffairs Committee there was "no reason
OL,10,Fwhy the Executive shouldn't have done
OL,11,Fits own open book process before".
OL,13,F"There's no reason why the Executive
OL,14,Fshouldn't have said to itself, 'right,
OL,15,Fwe've got all these pressures, what is
OL,16,Fabsolutely unavoidable? What is we'd
OL,17,Flike to do if we had the money but we
OL,18,Fdon't? So what are we going to do
OL,19,Fabout this?'.
OL,26,@qD@]OUsD@aO]uD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/15
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,415,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1784233115
OL,3,CRisk of 'Treasury always chickens out'
OL,4,Cmentality at Stormont, MPs told
OL,6,F"Rather than just saying 'pressure,
OL,7,Fpressure, pressure, here's a sum, how
OL,8,Fare you going to help us out?'.
OL,9,FBecause that is part of the
OL,10,Fresponsibility that comes with being
OL,11,Fin government."
OL,13,FMr Benn said it is his "hope" that he
OL,14,Fwill not have to set a budget for
OL,15,FNorthern Ireland, given that it "is
OL,16,Fthe responsibility of the Executive,
OL,17,Fand they should do their job".
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@OO]uD@XOUuD@]O]wD@aOUyD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/15
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,415,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1784233115
OL,3,CRisk of 'Treasury always chickens out'
OL,4,Cmentality at Stormont, MPs told
OL,6,F"As far as I'm aware, there has never
OL,7,Fbeen a circumstance in which, when the
OL,8,FExecutive is in being and the Assembly
OL,9,Fis meeting, that a UK government has
OL,10,Fset a budget for Northern Ireland," he
OL,11,Fsaid.
OL,13,F"There have been circumstances, of
OL,14,Fcourse, when the Executives come down
OL,15,Fwhere the government has done that,
OL,16,Fbut the institutions are there, the
OL,17,Fresponsibility is there with the
OL,18,FExecutive, and we are working with
OL,19,Fthem to try and find a way through
OL,20,Fthat but it is going to have to
OL,21,Finvolve setting a budget."
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@cO]uD@AOU}D@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/15
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
