CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1784233115
OL,3,CRisk of 'Treasury always chickens out'
OL,4,Cmentality at Stormont, MPs told
OL,6,FAsked what implications there are for
OL,7,Fthe Executive if they do not manage to
OL,8,Fstay within a set budget, Mr Benn
OL,9,Facknowledged "there is a bit of a
OL,10,Fpattern where the Government does ride
OL,11,Fin".
OL,13,F"The difficulty with that ` it is a
OL,14,Ffact ` is that some people may draw
OL,15,Fthe conclusion 'well, if we just sit
OL,16,Fhere, then someone will come and do
OL,17,Fthat again', and that is a challenge.
OL,26,@qD@NOUsD@CO]uD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/15
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,415,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1784233115
OL,3,CRisk of 'Treasury always chickens out'
OL,4,Cmentality at Stormont, MPs told
OL,6,FHe added: "I think my responsibility
OL,7,Fin advising the new prime minister,
OL,8,Fand that's all subject to what happens
OL,9,Fnext Monday, whoever is in this job,
OL,10,Fmy responsibility is to say 'this is
OL,11,Fthe work we've undertaken, this is
OL,12,Fwhat we know about the nature of the
OL,13,Ftrue pressures, these are the options
OL,14,Ffor doing something about it, these
OL,15,Fare the conditions that we would
OL,16,Fsuggest that we put in place in return
OL,17,Ffor any help ` if there is going to be
OL,18,Fany help'.
OL,26,@nD@KOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/15
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
